Hello @WillAyd! Thanks for updating this PR. We checked the lines you've touched for [PEP 8](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008) issues, and found:































* In the file [`pandas/core/internals/blocks.py`](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/ac7e76895b80314c78b246abb19a8764516123ae/pandas/core/internals/blocks.py):

> [Line 1835:5](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/ac7e76895b80314c78b246abb19a8764516123ae/pandas/core/internals/blocks.py#L1835): [E124](https://duckduckgo.com/?q=pep8%20E124) closing bracket does not match visual indentation





##### Comment last updated at 2019-03-11 19:40:33 UTC

One issue in existings that I wasn't sure how to resolve stems from the ExtensionBlock in internals, specifically this line:

https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/e28ae70ba8bd8b4174143543d1660421bc67887b/pandas/core/internals/blocks.py#L1693

It's superclass and all other subclasses derived therefrom treat this as an attribute, whereas here it's a property. I *think* that's the root of the issue

> One issue in existings that I wasn't sure how to resolve stems from the ExtensionBlock in internals, specifically this line:
> 
> [pandas/pandas/core/internals/blocks.py](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/e28ae70ba8bd8b4174143543d1660421bc67887b/pandas/core/internals/blocks.py#L1693)
> 
> Line 1693 in [e28ae70](/pandas-dev/pandas/commit/e28ae70ba8bd8b4174143543d1660421bc67887b)
>  def _can_hold_na(self): 
> 
> It's superclass and all other subclasses derived therefrom treat this as an attribute, whereas here it's a property. I _think_ that's the root of the issue

Interesting issue, it might be a bug in mypy. Although, it might also be a legitimate typing error: my guess would be that mypy is saying "you told me it's a property, so I expect that I can do `@Class.property.setter`, however, you also said it's `None` in which case `None.setter` is an error"
